Level 3: Building

Create Generator Functions in Python
Create generator functions using yield.
Define Instance Methods in Python
Define instance methods inside a class.
Override Methods and Dunder Methods in Python
Customize class behavior by overriding built-in behavior with dunder methods (e.g., __str__, __repr__), and override methods in a child class to customize behavior.
Use @property to Define Read-Only Attributes in Python
Use the @property decorator to create read-only attributes.
Handle Exceptions With Try-Except in Python
Use try-except blocks to handle exceptions gracefully. Handle specific exception types to provide targeted error handling. Use else and finally blocks in try-except structures to manage resources and cleanup.
Use Lambda Functions in Python
Use lambda functions for short, anonymous functions.
Create Enums with the enum Module in Python
Create enumerations using the enum module.
Use Context Managers in Python
Use a context manager to safely manage resources (e.g., file I/O).
Create Custom Context Managers in Python
Create custom context managers with __enter__ and __exit__ for reusable resource management.
Use Python’s logging Module
Use the logging module for structured logging.
Write Unit Tests and Validate Code Behavior in Python
Write unit tests using unittest or pytest. Use assert statements to validate code behavior. Use mocking and patching techniques in unit tests to isolate code.
Apply Duck Typing in Python
Apply duck typing in function and class design to create flexible and reusable code.
